items.name: Simply Comfy
items.description:
This is just an ULTRA simple ComfyUI workflow. It only has the Checkpoint, two Lora slots, and the positive and negative prompt zones. This is for people who are new to ComfyUI or just want something super fast and simple.

This workflow is for checkpoints that don't need a refiner such as SD 1.5 checkpoints as well as the many new SDXL models that don't require refiners.

You'll get an error message at first I'm sure as your checkpoints and loras will be in a different location than mine. Once you switch out the checkpoint and loras you should be good to go!

EDIT: This was my first ComfyUi workflow, I have a couple more up that, while slightly more complex, are more fun to work with. I encourage you to check them out and give them a spin! ğŸ˜€

  • trained for 28800 steps , 200 epochs with batch size 5 , at 3e-6 learning rate

items.name: crayon painting
items.description:
This model can produce a crayon effect and restore the feeling of children's original paintings.

Steps: 14,

Samplers: DMP++2s a Karras, DMP++2M Karras, DMP++SDE Karras,

Size: 512*768,

Weight: 0.9-1,

Trigger word + simple tag is enough, no need to add quality descriptors, nor negative words.

Recommended base models: dreamshaper, ghostMix, revAnimate_v122, AWPainting1.1, darkSushi Mix, TmndMix,

To draw the character 1girl/1boy, it is recommended to choose the above-mentioned models.

If you want to get closer to the shape of children's paintings, you can use anythingv5 and deliberate v2 base molds.

(Don't use "cute" tag, it may turn into a strange animal, haha!)

About the artist:

[From Wikipedia]

AmÃ©dÃ©e Ozenfant (15 April 1886 â€“ 4 May 1966) was a French cubist painter and writer. Together with Charles-Edouard Jeanneret (later known as Le Corbusier) he founded the Purist movement.

AmÃ©dÃ©e Ozenfant was one of the lesser-known cubism artist in modern French art history. However, he was influencial in shaping the way of modernism architecture together with Le Corbusier (father of modernism architecture).

The value of his artwork, expeicially his oil paintings with regard to still life objects (vase, glasses, tables guitars etc), lies on the fact that it directly established the aesthetic value of purism (together with Le Corbusier's artworks), which is the conceptual foundation behind mordenism architecture.

  • No more SDXL refiner model required to further improve the image quality;

  • Best to use 1024x1024 or higher resolution;

I'm happy to receive constructive feedbacks from anyone who's interested in artistic styles and concepts from established artists (either contemporary or past).

Milica Bogdanovna Jovovich[ (born December 17, 1975), known professionally as Milla Jovovich (MEE-lÉ™), is an American actress and model. Her starring roles in numerous science-fiction and action films led the music channel VH1 to deem her the "reigning queen of kick-butt" in 2006. In 2004, Forbes determined that she was the highest-paid model in the world.

Born in Kiev and raised in Los Angeles, Jovovich began modeling when Herb Ritts photographed her for the cover of the Italian magazine Lei in 1987. Richard Avedon featured her in Revlon's "Most Unforgettable Women in the World" advertisements. In 1988, Jovovich made her screen debut in the television film The Night Train to Kathmandu and appeared in her first feature film, Two Moon Junction.

Jovovich gained attention for her role in the 1991 romance film Return to the Blue Lagoon, as she was 15 years old at the time. She was considered to have a breakthrough with her role in the 1997 French science-fiction action film The Fifth Element, written and directed by Luc Besson. She and Besson married that year, but soon divorced. She starred as the heroine and martyr in Besson's The Messenger: The Story of Joan of Arc (1999). From 2002 to 2016, Jovovich portrayed Alice in the action horror film franchise Resident Evil, which became the highest-grossing film series to be based on video games.

Jovovich released a debut album, The Divine Comedy, in 1994, and a follow-up, The People Tree Sessions, in 1998. She continues to release demos for other songs on her official website and frequently contributes to film soundtracks. In 2003, model Carmen Hawk and she created the clothing line Jovovichâ€“Hawk, which ran until 2008. Jovovich has her own production company, Creature Entertainment.

items.description:
Tulpas are also called imaginary friends, and are fictitious beings created to protect their personalities.

In Anime and game worlds, they act as peripherals that allow the protagonist to experience reality-altering paranormal phenomena.

The prince may be cursed to become a tulpa.

In some cases, the main character girl likes him in the state of talpa.

However, there is no guarantee that she will like the reverted tulpa.

Tulpas lose their voice or become invisible when they or their master reach adulthood.
